@codelipenghui Thanks for the fix. 
Seems there was some thing wrong in UT. Please reference the failure tests at this link:
https://builds.apache.org/job/pulsar_precommit_java8/4789/#showFailuresLink

@chrismiller thanks for reporting this.  I pushed a commit to your PR with my proposed fix

I have removed the code in the JSONSchema that was causing the problem.  The original reason we added that code was so that fields from child classes don't get serialized if the schema is set to the base class.  However, after some thinking, I don't think this is necessary and likely impossible to accomplish given the problem @chrismiller described.  I think its ok to still serialize the field of child classes and write them to a topic given that you can read them out on the consumer end as the base class which currently you can.  So I don't see a point to going down the rabbit hole of how not to serialize child class fields.  We might even want this behavior given that users can evolve their schema over time.

@sijie @srkukarni @merlimat @ivankelly what do you think?

@rdhabalia I see. Then this change would be a superset of #899 (in the sense that it would allow to achieve that goal as well), am I right? 

Would it then make sense to deprecate the sub prefix mode feature and just rely on "per-subscription" authorization?

cc/ @nkurihar

@merlimat - The logic for how proxyRoles should be used for admin calls was inconsistent with the way it is used for nonadmin operations, and the tests were written in compliance with the new inconsistent logic.

I have fixed the tests and the code. 

@ivankelly - can you help review the fixes.
